# Session and games

See `architecture.mdc` for SOLID / DRY / YAGNI / KISS.

## Layers (strict)

```
page.tsx / components  ->  hooks  ->  server/*  ->  prisma
                              \->  session-engine/* (pure, no I/O)
```

- `src/session-engine/` - dice, room events, validators (pure TS, unit tested)
- `src/server/` - business logic + Prisma; returns typed DTOs, not raw Prisma models to UI
- `src/hooks/` - data fetching glue for client components
- `src/components/bridge/` - host UI only
- `src/components/player/` - mobile-first player UI only
- `src/app/api/` - thin handlers: validate -> service -> JSON

## Anti-patterns (reject in review)

```tsx
// BAD - logic in component
export function RollButton() {
  const result = Math.floor(Math.random() * 20) + 1;
  await db.sessionEvent.create({ ... });
}

// GOOD
import { rollD20 } from '@/session-engine/dice';
import { useRequestRoll } from '@/hooks/use-request-roll';
```

- No `prisma` import in `components/` or `hooks/` that only serve UI
- No 300-line "god components"; extract `*-view.tsx` + `use-*.ts`

## Game content

- Stored in PostgreSQL (`GameTemplate`, scenes), not hardcoded in React
- Seed `el-dorado` via migration or seed script
- `titleRu`/`titleEn`, `contentRu`/`contentEn` on scenes

## Host editor

- CRUD game metadata, acts/scenes, image upload to S3
- `hostOnlyNotes` never exposed to player API or websocket payloads

## Player API

- Read-only session state for players; no host fields
- Touch targets 44px+, `env(safe-area-inset-*)` on full-height layouts

## Realtime

- Events match `RoomEvent` union in session-engine
- Validate on server before broadcast and DB insert
